Explanation.name: Color
Explanation.description: controls how the color of the particle changes as a function of its input

Explanation.name: Alpha
Explanation.description: seperate from color, controls how the particle fades as a function of its input

Explanation.name: Scale
Explanation.description: controls how the size of a particle changes as a function of its input

Explanation.name: Rotation
Explanation.description: controls how the particle rotates. 0= 0 degrees, .5= 180 degrees, 1.0= 360 degrees

Explanation.name: Frame index
Explanation.description: provides finer grain control over how the animation happens. a output of 0.25 means that when that input is fed in, the particle will be 25% of the way through its animation.

Explanation.name: Spawned Effects
Explanation.description: collision occurs when particle physics has collision, death spawned when particle dies

TagReference.name: collision effect
TagReference.description: effect, material effect or sound spawned when this particle collides with something

TagReference.name: death effect
TagReference.description: effect, material effect or sound spawned when this particle dies

Explanation.name: Attached Particle Systems
Explanation.description: Locations: up - particles shoot straight up gravity - particles shoot straight down NONE - opposite of particle direction

Explanation.name: MARKER NAMES
Explanation.description:
In addition to the marker in the render model there are several special marker names:
replace Replace allows you to use the same effect with different markers. Damage transition effects support this for example.
gravity, up The direction of gravity (down) and the opposite direction (up). Always supplied
normal Vector pointing directly away from the surface you collided with. Supplied for effects from collision.
forward The 'negative incident' vector i.e. the direction the object is moving in. Most commonly used to generated decals. Supplied for effects from collision.
backward The 'incident' vector i.e. the opposite of the direction the object is moving in. Supplied for effects from collision.
reflection The way the effect would reflect off the surface it hit. Supplied for effects from collision.
root The object root (pivot). These can used for all effects which are associated with an object.
impact The location of a havok impact.

ShortInteger.name: sort bias
ShortInteger.description: use values between -10 and 10 to move closer and farther from camera (positive is closer)

RealEulerAngles2D.description: particle initial velocity direction relative to the location's forward
